abstract: To change course, the country’s leaders must take on the moneyed elite and religious extremism.
snippet: To change course, the country’s leaders must take on the moneyed elite and religious extremism.
lead_paragraph: If an airplane took off a dozen times only to come crashing down each time, the only logical conclusion would be that the aircraft requires a fundamental redesign. Pakistan’s economy, like the airplane, has crashed 13 times in the last 60 years, each time requiring an International Monetary Fund bailout.
